latestPosts.caption: Its okay if you were on survival mode this year. Not everyone’s “vision boards” and “resolutions” came to life ✍🏼❤️‍🩹

I used to believe hacks don’t work until i tried these 🙂‍↔️🙏🏽🎀

( best hack, makeup hacks , underpainting hack, perfume layering, perfume hack, tubing mascara)

Here’s what i think about the new @kaybykatrina velvet creme blush 🎀

The blush definitely feels & looks luxurious 💰
Extremely pigmented but blends quite effortlessly.
Yes I applied a decent amount to show the colour payoff, can be toned down as your liking.
Is very smooth creamy velvety to touch 😍🧈
Has a cream to powder finish, no need to set
Lasts fairly long for about 5-6 hours 

My disappointment lies in this shade in particular which showed up different on my cheeks like almost a plumy deep pink than how it looks in the pan which is a deep dark browny red on the pan. 🙂
Lastly, it is pricey so if you decide to get it, always wait for the sale 🙂‍↔️

( kay beauty , kay beauty velvet creme blush , kay beauty blush awaken , kay by katrina , cream blush, blush blindness )

A multipurpose product with refillable packaging? Yes please!

I love this blush, it’s pigmented, smooth and blends so well. The shade will be my winter blush 🥰
The crème highlighter is what dreams are made of. It is multipurpose, you can wear it on your eyelids and cheeks. 
They are creamy, blendable and non chalky.

The best part? Get your customised bundle and enjoy more savings 😉🎁

( asa beauty , clean makeup , winter makeup )

new fav 🍂❄️ blush unlocked 

A gorg creamy bronzy terracotta shade i instantly fell in 🫶🏽 with
.. also such a perfect blonzing shade 
🧸

@asabeautyindia lip & cheek tint in “ripe raspberry”
Thank me later 😙

( fall blush , rhode toasted teddy dupe , cream blush , lip and cheek tint , terracotta blush, blonzing )

🪞✨🫰🏼

Internet made me.. 🫨

Milk Skin Toner was nice, lightweight yet very hydrating. Felt tacky which i love in toners 🥛

Cushion Foundation has some crazy coverage (not full) but still looks natural. The applicator is all you need gives a seamless filter like finish. 
Expected this to be more glowy than it is. Dry skin people prep your skin well. 

The cushion applicator of the mini size is tiny so i had to go in multiple times but one dip is enough to cover whole face. 

Well, to be fair i haven’t tried any cushion foundation before so i can’t tell if its extraordinary than the rest!

Shade i bought: 24N LATTE
(I could have gone one shade darker)
